            ? he said he did not say so, but that the man lived there from whom he had the flute. I told him I wanted to examine him; he opened the door, looked spitefully back at me, and ran away; I followed him, and called Stop thief, and he was taken. He said before the justice, he found it on Tower-hill.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence.</p>
